full_text: INSTRUCTIONS Screened by NARA, 9/18/2023 On line 4, if entry was without inspection, strike out the printed language and insert E. W. I., at port or nearest point of entry and date, i.e. "E.W.I. 2 mi. east ELP 5-6-60" If entry was as a crewman insert status of admission; vessel, date and place of arrival and date and place of desertion, i.e. "D-1 SS Cosmic NYC 3/12/61 - Deserted BAL 3/20/61." On lines 8 and 9, if alien is in possession of document other than a visa, insert type, number, place and date of issuance, i.e. "BCC # 138965 ELP 15-60 Give careful attention to the data reported in the Narrative. Include date, exact time and place, and manner of entry. If assistance rendered, furnish full details Furnish circumstances of arrest if not routine. State details of travel while in the U.S. including all perti- nent intelligence information Status at entry, status when found, and length of time illegally in the U.S. shall conform to those cate- gories under Parts I, II and III, Form G-23.12. Use code word for deportation charges. In interview cases furnish full details as to health, humanitarian aspects, and the information required in G-135 block below. Furnish information copy to appropriate CPI and/or DD when required by O.I. 103.1 (a) and 103.1(b). If an alien has claimed U. S. citizenship or prosecution is contemplated, fill out form I-215a. If an alien is required to be registered, check the block marked "Alien Registration." NARRATIVE (Continued) Los Angeles, California. Mrs Hyppolite is a nurse by profession.
